<TEXTAREA NAME="ReplyMessage" ROWS=20 COLS=75 WRAP="VIRTUAL">[QUOTE]Originally posted by Arhu:
[I]Well, I agree, too (with this stats stuff - I dunno exactly what is meant, but see below).
But now hear [i]my[/i] thoughts.

[b]Party vs. Single Character[/b]
Bean and Bronthion have pointed out an interesting quality of a party: interaction. But you are right that the identification with a single character is much easier than with an entire party. I never played Fallout but the NPC part is a good way of creating a "virtual" party, it would seem. Those refused three characters could join you on your journeys and have a life of their own or, more like BG, be restricted controllable by the player. However, IMO they should in this case be rather independent so the player can focus on [i]his[/i] identity, but he should still be able to controll the inventory or so of the others, for example. On the other hand, the hero should also be able to chose to walk alone with no handicap to his travel.

[b]Experience Points[/b]
Yes, EP are more than just a pool for level ups. They should reflect all the knowledge, wisdom and skills a character got on his travels. Accordingly I think the "research plate" is a nice way to handle experience points. [i]But[/i], as Bean and Bobby mentioned above, you don't merely "research" your skills, you [i]learn[/i] them. But while thinking about it, I like the idea. What about researching (or [i]learning[/i]) your basic skills (i.e. swimming, climbing etc.) and later improve them by using them? This improvement, however, would have to be restricted. As Bobby said, players would spent their whole time swimming and running around... Anyway I like the dependency of related skills.

[b]Stats[/b]
I think the stats should be used in a wide variety of actions. Dialogs are one possibility (see Bean's post about Fallout). I don't know exactly what the stats could be used for, so comments of other humans are required, but I have some (spongy) ideas:

Intelligence:
In my opinion, this improves magic abilities, reading, combination, languages, knowledge etc. and could be used, for example, in difficult situations where a decision has to be made on given facts or where unknown artifacts come to play. So, Int. could possibly be improved by reading skills.

Strength:
Carrying power, melee combat, stamina etc.. Could be linked with climbing and running skills.

Dexterity:
Reflects how agile a character can move or handle weapons... Again running skills come to mind.

Charisma:
Should directly affect reactions of other persons and to other persons, dialogs, costs of Weapons and other stuff, depending on the sex of a character.

Intuition:
Hearing, sight, sixth sense, ...

Other: There are other attributes I didn't mention. I just wanted to make some suggestions.

[i]Miauh...[/i]
Arhu

PS: Lar, next time try to split your questions etc. into some parts. It's (at least for me   ;) ) somewhat difficult to keep track of all the answers...
PPS: Rat, uh.. of course you're right..   ;)

[This message has been edited by Arhu (edited 06-11-1999).][/I][/QUOTE]

</TEXTAREA>
